\section{Initial constraints}
\begin{itemize}
\item $i_0$, \dots, $i_{13}$ range from 1 to 9.
\item $v_0=1$ if $13=i_0$, 0 otherwise (so $v_0=0$).
\item $v_1=1$ if $v_0=0$, 0 otherwise (so $v_1=1$).
\item $v_2=1$ if $i_0\bmod 26 + 11 = i_0 + 11 = i_1$, 0 otherwise (so $v_2=0$).
\item $v_3=1$ if $v_2=0$, 0 otherwise (so $v_3=1$).
\item $v_4=1$ if $(i_1+3)\bmod 26 + 14 = i_1+17 = i_2$, 0 otherwise (so $v_4=0$).
\item $v_5=1$ if $v_4=0$, 0 otherwise (so $v_5=1$).
\item $v_6=1$ if $(i_2+8)\bmod 26 - 5=i_2+3=i_3$, 0 otherwise (so unclear).
\item $v_7=1$ if $v_6=0$, 0 otherwise (so unclear).
\item $v_8=1$ if $(\textrm{complex expression} \bmod 26) + 14 = i_4$, 0 otherwise (so $v_8=0$).
\item $v_9=1$ if $v_8=0$, 0 otherwise (so $v_9=1$).
\item $v_{10}=1$ if $(i_4+13)\bmod 26 + 10 = i_5$, 0 otherwise (so $v_{10}=0$).
\item $v_{11}=1$ if $v_{10}=0$ (so $v_{11}=1$).
\item $v_{12}=1$ if $(i_5+9)\bmod 26+12=i_6$, 0 otherwise (so $v_{12}=0$).
\item $v_{13}=1$ if $v_{12}=0$ (so $v_{13}=1$).
\item $v_{14}=1$ if $(i_6+6)\bmod 26-14=i_6-8=i_7$, 0 otherwise (so unclear).
\item $v_{15}=1$ if $v_{14}=0$, 0 otherwise (so unclear).
\item $v_{16}=1$ if
\begin{align*}
  \Bigl(v_{15}(i_7+1) + (25v_{15}+1) 
   \Bigl(&26i_4 + i_5 + 26^2 v_7(i_3+5) \\
    &+26^2(25v_7+1)(\textrm{expr})+\Bigl\lfloor\frac{i_6}{26}+\frac{43}{13}\Bigr\rfloor\Bigr)\Bigr)\bmod 26 - 8 = i_8,
\end{align*}
which reduces to
\[
  \bigl(v_{15}(i_7+1) +(25v_{15}+1)(i_5+3)\bigr)\bmod 26 - 8 = i_8,
\]
which is so far unclear.
\item $v_{17}=1$ if $v_{16}=0$, 0 otherwise, so unclear.
\item $v_{18}=1$ if $(\textrm{complicated expression})\bmod 26 +13 = i_9$, 0 otherwise, so $v_{18}=0$.
\item $v_{19}=1$ if $v_{18}=0$, so $v_{19}=1$.
\item $v_{20}=1$ if $i_9+2=i_10$, 0 otherwise, so unclear.
\item $v_{21}=1$ if $v_{20}=0$, 0 otherwise, so unclear.
\item $v_{22}=1$ through $v_{27}$ are all determined by complicated expressions.
\end{itemize}

\section{Constraints from the tail end}

We want $v_{27}(i_{13} + 15) + (25v_{27} + 1)(\textrm{complex nonnegative expression}) = 0$. We must therefore have $v_{27}=0$ and $v_{26}=1$. (We will figure out how to do this later.)

From here the constraints are too complex to approach directly. Instead (after some brute-force exploration) I guessed that $v_{2n}=1$ and $v_{2n+1}=0$ for all $n$ where these were not yet determined. This gave several equations relating the digits which were easy to satisfy with a greedy search.


